                <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00 Washington/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-13T16:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 14—3:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. It is my impression after an interview with the President today that an
                    invitation from the Secretary of State for the December conference under recent
                        <hi rend="italic">Tacoma</hi> agreement to be held in Washington would be
                    gladly accepted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ramer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
